article.headline: Pondexter scores game's final seven points
article.linkText: Rutgers rallies to stun No. 17 Ohio State
article.story:
PISCATAWAY, N.J. (AP) -- Cappie Pondexter scored the game's final
seven points -- including a decisive 3-point basket with 5.4 seconds
remaining -- to give Rutgers a 56-53 victory Sunday over Ohio
State (No. 17 ESPN/USA Today, No. 18 AP).

Rutgers (7-4) was trailing 53-49 when Pondexter made a 3-pointer
with 1:09 to play to pull Rutgers within a point. Ohio State (9-3)
turned over the ball on the ensuing possession, and Jessica
Davenport fouled Pondexter with 23 seconds to go.

Pondexter tied the game by making one of two free throws, and
Chelsea Newton rebounded the miss to set up the game-winning shot.

Ohio State's Kim Wilburn was unable to get a shot off in the
final five seconds, giving Rutgers its second victory this season
over a top-25 team. The Scarlet Knights improved to 6-0 a home.

Newton led Rutgers with 16 points, and Pondexter and Shalicia
Hurns had 13 apiece. LaToya Turner paced the Buckeyes with 15
points, and Stephanie Blanton added 10.

A steal by Nikki Jett and layup by Newton gave Rutgers a 41-40
lead with 8:50 to play, but the Buckeyes responded with a 6-0 run
to go ahead 46-41.

Newton's jumper tied the score at 49 with three minutes left,
but Davenport's basket put Ohio State ahead. Then Turner scored on
a putback to give the Buckeyes their 53-49 lead.

Rutgers held a 27-24 halftime lead behind nine points from Hurns
and six from Newton. The first half featured six ties and five lead
changes.
